<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 5:01PM MDT  by NWS Spokane</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Bonner
and northwestern Shoshone Counties through 430 PM PDT...
At 400 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles southwest of Noxon, or 22 miles north of Kellogg, moving north
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Jordan Creek Campground.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
